Text.string: Vault Thief!
Another perfect livescream from our infallible God-Queen Tyreen. The Holy Broadcast Center opens once again, to hear your sins and receive your skins!
Step forward and be CLEANSED!
Kneel and accept your JUDGMENT!
I speak for the CALYPSOS!
Oh, and if Lilith the Firehawk steps to me again, that bird's gonna get plucked.
Yoink.
Gotcha.
Perfection.
Nothin' to it.
If ya want, you can try hijacking a vehicle. Ain't nothing to it. Just run up to one and kindly tell the driver to skedaddle.
Go on, Vault Hunter. March on up to the car of your choice and kick the driver out!
Don't be shy. Pick a car and throw the driver out. That's how we do 'round here.
If you want wheels, yer gon' have to take a vehicle by force.
Now, I never had trouble grabbin' bandit attention. I'd start the show with a bare hamhock. Then they'd get the bare-knuckle encore. Bam!
Let's turn up the beatings-per-minute!
That all you got?! Let's pump it up!
Tyreen Calypso turned that entire clan into dust. She's not just a bandit warlord. She's a Siren.
Scabrazor55, my lovely! Me and Troy got the shirts you sent, and we'll send a pic of us wearing them on the show just as... soon as we get the torsos out.
Props to Crudguzzler! You had the guts to tattoo my name directly onto your eyeballs, and I'm... guessing you're blind now, but still, wow! Such dedication to the cause!

Now a shoutout to PocketRocketBoy who sacrificed seven Crimson Raider scalps to the offering box!||Oooh, just getting word now that PocketRocketBoy blew off his balls with a... well, live and learn, I guess.
Big thanks to HardBard2 who sent us his own thumb! At least, we're assuming it's his, since the letter he wrote was completely illegible.
Shout out to the follower who left me that skag tongue necklace! It's... surrounded by a halo of flies and I just absolutely adore it!

Very special thanks to our followers Brittletooth and Natch. Your recipe for live-roasted Crimson Raider, armor and all, was—mmh!—to die for! And the footage of the meal! Just... wow. Make sure to leave room for a Vault Thief or two, ya crazy kids.

Heyyyyy, Meatstreak3r—ooh, E is a 3, that's nice—huge props for your gi-normous donation this week! It'll take us awhile to sort through those arms and engine parts, but it is SO worth it! When we open the Great Vault, you'll be there!
And the winner of the raffle is... Scumcrank! Scumcrank, you've won a lifetime supply of skin pizzas, courtesy of the Bloodblender Clan! Sling Mouthpiece an ECHO for details.
This next one goes out to a very special tink, Throttlejaw, whose rocket ride almost hit the Vault Thieves' bus. So close. We'll remember you!

Special shoutout to Snotworm77, who's now the record holder for Pandora's longest intestinal jumprope! Oh—six miles, damn, that's a half mile longer than the previous record holder!||Who will now be executed for their failure.
The Skagbloat Clan has made the top five offerings for the past three months! We could wrap the moon of Elpis in the flayed skins they've sent us! That's... that's a lot of skin.
Be sure to follow xXBileDozerXx delivering re-animated re-enactments of all your favorite Let's Flays twice-weekly! If you have spare corpses or a background in puppetry, shoot an ECHO her way.

Map? Uh... if you're talkin' about that alien junk, my clan is bringing it to the Calypso Twins as an offering! They're heading to the Holy Broadcast Center. It's where the Calypsos host murder-sermons to amp up their followers.

We can't let the Calypsos get that map. But the Holy Broadcast Center is a long ride. Vault Hunter, you're gonna need some wheels. My friend Ellie runs the Catch-A-Ride. Go introduce yourself, and she'll hook you up.
Vaughn, what the hell? You knew I've been looking for that map. Why didn't you bring it to me?
Woah-woah-woah-hohoho, okay, okay. I see what happened here. Let me explain. Uh, I let the map slip into the hands of culty psychopaths, and now the whole galaxy is in danger.
Yeah. That's what I was saying.
Okay, same page! You know what this calls for? Apology push-ups.
You don't have to... ugh.
(push-up effort)
(push-up effort)
Ahhh! Come on!
Yeah! You gotta want it!
Yeah! Want it!
Yeah! Push it!
Hwuuuh—I'm sorry!
Hwuuuh—I apologize!
Fwuuuh—I was wrong!
Fwuuuh—I'm so sorry!
Ghhuhh—Please like me!
Ghnngh—I didn't mean it!
(push-up effort)
Hnnuuh—Sorry!
(push-up effort)
(push-up effort)
(push-up effort)
(push-up effort)
(push-up effort)
Oh, yeah! C'mon!
Yeah! Do it!
Ellie got you rollin'? She always does. Now head to the Holy Broadcast Center and find that map.

Yo, Vault Hunter. So that road will take you right to the Holy Broadcast Center. Watch out for those so-called “Twin Gods”! From what I hear, Tyreen Calypso's the star of the show. Her brother Troy runs the cult's propaganda. P.S., they both suck. Just sayin'.

Now, I've never seen the Calypsos myself, but they must be the most terrifying, bloodthirsty psychopaths Pandora's ever seen. I mean, look—my clan only accepted me as a leader after I killed a guy with just my abs, so imagine what it takes to unite all the clans together. You'd need like... a twenty-pack. Eighteen, bare mins.

I know my clan betrayed me, but, if the Calypsos mess with my Sun Smashers then we have got a blood feud on our hands! Which would be awesome! Been a while since I got a good old fashioned blood feud going! Four and oh, baby!
All right, time to welcome the Sun Smashers into our family! We'll post the vid later, along with some new Let's Flays! Signing off for now. Don't forget to like, follow, and obey.
But first, loyal followers, our Holy Broadcast Center is being defiled by a heretic. Cleanse our hallowed halls with their blood!
Vault Map in my sights.
Va va, I knew I'd find the Vault Map.
A-ha! The Vault Map! There you are!
What's that there? The Vault Map?
Vault Hunter—you really got the map?
Mission accomplished, Firehawk.
It's in good hands, Firehawk. Mine, to be precise.
Yes, Firehawk. A successful hunt!
Course I did, Firehawk! I always get the job done.
Just Lilith is fine.
Didn't find the map, so I brought a bandit instead.
Map wasn't there, so I took this bandit instead.
The map was not there, so I acquired this bandit.
The map was gone, but I picked meself up a bandit souvenir!

Ugh, I hate the Calypso Twins so much! They conned the bandits of Pandora with promises of death cars and meat storms and blood saunas—good stuff, right? I mean, even my clan fell for it! Gullible idiots.
Over here, Vault Hunter!
And now, the moment you've been waiting for! Let loose your bloodlust roar for our God-Queen, the First Sister, Tyreen Calypso!

What up, my bandit orphans? God-Queen Tyreen, comin' at you live from the HBC. We're streamin', you're screamin', and we're all preparin' to get into the Great Vault! Got some new converts today, and guess what? They brought us the sacred Vault Map! If that doesn't earn them a special place in the family, I don't know what does. But first, I wanna get real for sec. You've all accepted me, even though I wasn't born a bandit. My first words weren't “blood feud” or “ribcage spelunker”. But now we're all family. And family is forever. We'll start the ceremony after a few quick shout-outs. Stay bloodthirsty!
Welcome to the Holy Broadcast Center. Our daily livescream will be starting shortly, with a special guest!
Vault Thief...
You... will... DIE!

Did you come all this way for that busted-ass map, or are you just here to see me? Didn't know you were such a superfan! Well, ya missed the show! Oh, right. Bet you're all like, “What's up with those husks?” Well, it's a thing I do. Check out the screens.
(screams of total agony)
So, I offered the Sun Smashers a place in our family, but they just wanted guns and cash. They betrayed the family. Oh! Then Troy said something great.
Gods don't negotiate.
“Gods don't negotiate!” I love it. Love it!
Like I said, that map is super busted, so go ahead and take it. I'll swing by later to pick it up. You're my most loyal follower, Vault Thief. Ya just don't know it yet.
You got the map? Nice! So... did you see any of my Sun Smashers? And why do you smell like dust and skin?
Tyreen Calypso murdered your whole clan, Vaughn. TPK. Nothin' I could do.
Your clan was murdered by Tyreen Calypso. I was too late to stop her.
Your clan is dead. Tyreen Calypso slaughtered them. It was... unnatural.
Murder party. Extremely dead. Tyreen Calypso did it. Condolences.
Damn it! I never told them... I... NO! Sun Smashers never cry.||If Tyreen Calypso wants a blood feud, she's got one!||BLOOD FEUUUUD!
I knew you'd find the map, killer. Bring it back, and don't let it out of your sight. I lost it once. I won't lose it again.
I knew the COV was dangerous. But it's even worse than I thought.
Well, you're almost to the Holy Broadcast Center, Vault Hunter. If you see my Sun Smasher bros and bronettes, tell them Vaughn said... you just tell them Vaughn said “yo”.
Give your offerings now so you can join our elite, Eridium-tier chat for behind-the-scenes murder and mayhem!
Now remind me. What'd ya say you was gonna do to my gal-pal Lil?
God-Queen Tyreen will drink soup from the skull of the Great Heretic!||—Aghh!
My bad! Finger slipped. Hah! Heh-heh, heh!
Oh, howdy! Didn't see ya there!
I heard ya'll were in the neighborhood. Good to see ol' Lil found some new blood! I'm Ellie. Hey. What are ya staring at, hon?
Damn, you're sturdy. It'd take an army to knock you down.
You look hard to knock down. Could've used you during training.
Most humans are frail and weak—but you've got admirable heft, girl.
You're a natural with that rocket launcher. My kinda girl!
Ain't you a heart-breaker! Lil said you was looking for a vehicle. Damn cultists stole all mine. Mind stealing me one back? Then I'll set ya up with the Catch-A-Ride.
And thanks for comin' by!
Mmm, that is a sight! Can't tell what was better—the comin' or the goin'! I'm sayin' you got a nice ass.

You know, I miss the old bandits. Now they're all Children of the Vault. You'd have to have a twice-baked skag turd for a brain to believe those cult leaders. Tyreen Calypso is just a sexy rabble-rouser. And her brother Troy is creepier than a slow dance with a hot corpse.
That hunka junk'll do. Drive it on back, now, hon.
All right! Now register with the Catch-A-Ride so you can digistruct a new one whenever you want—just in case you get a Pandora flat, meanin' your car explodes.
Got a rocket launcher I've been testin'. All yours, sweet thang. Just make sure you equip it.
All set! Happy hunting. You tell Lil our ship's almost ready. Soon as she finds that map, we're good to go!

Been here by my lonesome for awhile. Lil asked me to fix up a new ship for the Raiders. My late brother was working on one in his spare time... when he wasn't huffing biofuel or thinking about boobies. Then he was killed by one. A ship, that is. Though Scooter would've rather gone out smushed to death by a big ol' titty. Wouldn't we all?
Just park yer car there, hon.
Park there, Vault Hunter.
Park the car, hon.
You stargazin', Vault Hunter? All ya need to do is park yer car.
I can't register your vehicle until you park it, sweet stuff.
